The indexing service for pages currently runs against the raw HTML code inside the HTML macro. It would be preferable if the rendered text was indexed instead, either by rendering the HTML or just extracting visible text from HTML tags, because search results are much more readable. 

For example, {html}<p>Test</p>{html} is currently indexed as <p>Test</p> but should be indexed as Test.

