Confluence (and JIRA) is very nice in that it converts urls in text automatically to links.  An example is http://jira.atlassian.com.  This only work in tables if there is a blank prior to the link as the following example shows:
{noformat}
|http://jira.atlassian.com|
| http://jira.atlassian.com|
{noformat}
|http://jira.atlassian.com|
| http://jira.atlassian.com|

The request is to make them work the same.  First it is hard to explain to people why it works sometimes and not other times.  Second, it would be helpful when bringing in data from other sources like csv files (csv macro) and similar.

