Hello,

the bad characters in title page are not configurable. Somme characters are rejected by our SSO.

The error message is "Page titles can not contain (:, @, /, \, |, ^, #, ;, [, ], {, }, <, >) or start with ($, .., ~)".

This characters are hard coded in AbstractPage.java :
{code}
private static final char[] invalidTitleCharacters = new char[]{':', ';', '<', '>', '@', '/', '\\', '|', '#', '[', ']', '{', '}', '^'};
{code}

This characters should be configured with regexp for exemple. Is there improvements planned?

Regards,
Pierre

